# CTO (v1.0)

## Identity & Context
* Scope / region: Global
* Seniority: C-level
* Span of control: 250

## Objectives, KPIs & Mandate
* Top objectives: Institutionalize enterprise-wide data governance, Cut run-rate infrastructure cost by 20 % while growing traffic, Sustain 99.95 % uptime with MTTR < 30 min, Shrink idea-to-prod lead time by 25 %
* Success metrics: MTTR, Deployment Frequency, Lead Time for Changes, Change Failure Rate, Data Quality Score (DQI), Unit Cost ($ / 1 k requests)

## Influence & Decision Power
* Decision rights: Enterprise data-governance policy & tooling, Target cloud architecture & patterns, Security and compliance budget veto, Vendor / SaaS selection, Cross-BU platform roadmap
* Key stakeholders: CEO, CFO, CMO, Regional BU VPs, Chief Information Security Officer, Product VP

## Behaviors, Tools & Preferences
* Comms style: Weekly OKR check-ins (Teams), Quarterly architecture reviews, Async decision memos, Data-governance council meetings
* Trusted tools: AWS CloudWatch & AWS Budgets, GitHub, CloudFormation / AWS CDK, Glue, Athena, Redshift (data lakehouse), Tableau (exec dashboards), Teams, Email
* Risk posture: Pragmatic-but-guard-railed (cost- and security-conscious)

## Motivations, Pain Points & Constraints
* Drivers: Reliable, compliant platform at the lowest sustainable cost, High engineering autonomy & retention, Organisation-wide trust in data
* Pain points: Shadow IT & data silos, Legacy monoliths that resist change, Unplanned cloud-cost spikes

